# Single n8n write webhook the frontend calls directly (no Python backend in prod).
# Copy to .env for local dev; set the same var in the Netlify dashboard
# (Site settings -> Environment variables) so it is baked at build time.
# Only VITE_-prefixed vars are exposed to the browser.
#
# Stock is seeded + tracked in the frontend (localStorage). This webhook only
# logs winners: each win POSTs { name, goodie_id, label } to append the guest to
# the Google Sheet guest list; the response is ignored.
# Leave blank to run in MOCK mode (no network / no guest-list logging; spins still work).

VITE_N8N_WRITE_URL=https://your-n8n-host/webhook/<id>

# CORS: the n8n Webhook node must allow this site's origin. Set the node's
# "Allowed Origins (CORS)" to your Netlify domain (or * while testing).

# Gift page (gift.html): sync webhook. The frontend POSTs
# { name, email, phone, photo_base64 } and n8n responds 200 with { image_url }
# after generating the hug image (and appending the lead to a sheet).
# Leave blank to run the gift page in MOCK mode (returns mascot.png, no network).
VITE_N8N_GIFT_URL=https://your-n8n-host/webhook/<gift-id>
